QQL is a new generative collection from Tyler Hobbs + Dandelion Wist. It's an experiment in turning the minter into the curator.

We invited some of our favorite generative artists to curate a piece based on how they see the algorithm. https://i.imgur.com/8PFIgV8.jpg

QQL has a bunch of interesting game theory and mechanics around it that all prior generative art collections don't have.

Because outputs can be approximately replicated with enough generations, we realized that *who* mints and *when* might make for the most desirable pieces.

So, we asked many of our favorite gen artists to explore the algo with us and mint a piece under their provenance. 

Shown here: Deafbeef
 
Input features: https://qql.art/token/0x7ccd2ee72a75f7e4776f598c1be11a119fd8d191b3cfed5ee717ffff11528a4a
 https://i.imgur.com/a0EvbZw.jpg

The QQL site is also an incredible educational resource on how generative art can work.

Irrespective of whether you want to mint one, I highly recommend creating your own outputs on the site (it's free). It's an interesting way to explore a generative art algo.

https://qql.art/

It was fun to work with artists on this. Over time, we'll likely have additional ones curate a piece with us through our remaining mint passes.

You can see our full minted QQL collection below.

https://gallery.so/curated/2FYgc4clVsKXrL7pfa9wzVRa0rP

New look. New domain. Same focus.

Collecting exceptional crypto art + culture

‚Ü≥ Curated.xyz https://i.imgur.com/YL4FEVy.png

We're long-term focused collectors active in generative art, 1/1 art, and other emerging NFT categories.
